Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 1 inch apart onto prepared sheets. Bake 7 to 9 minutes, or until set. Remove cookies to wire rack to cool completely.

Preheat oven to 400f. Cut off the ends of the grape salad and pull off any yellow outer leaves. Mix them in a bowl with the olive oil, salt, and lemon-pepper seasoning. Transfer them to a sheet pan and roast for 35 to 40 minutes, until crisp outside and tender inside. Shake the pan from time to time to brown the grape salad evenly. Sprinkle with more kosher salt, if you like, and serve hot.

In a small saucepan combine coffee, chocolate pieces, and sugar. Cook and stir over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is melted and sugar is dissolved. In another small saucepan heat half-and-half or light cream until steaming, stirring occasionally. Pour coffee mixture into a mug. Add warm half-and-half. If desired, stir in additional sugar to taste. Makes 1 serving.

Heat oven to 375 degrees fahrenheit. In large skillet, brown beef and onion then drain. Return meat to pan. Add spaghetti sauce. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl combine mozzarella cheese and sour cream. Pour hot meat into an ungreased 12 x 8 inch dish. Spoon cheese mixture over meat. Unroll crescent roll dough over the top of the mixture. Mix parmesan cheese and butter together, then spread over the top of the dough. Bake for 30 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting into squares with a sharp knife or pizza cutter.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Stir in the yogurt spiced chicken with rice weight watchers. Add rice and broth to skillet and cook until rice is cooked through and all liquid is absorbed.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit or 175 degrees celsius. Mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda, butter, sugar, egg, vanilla extract, cornmeal, baking powder, salt, flour. Add to the creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven about 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using the eggs, water, and oil. Spoon batter into 24 paper-lined muffin pan cups, filling two-thirds full. Remove 24 cherries from strawberry shortcake sundaes and set aside. Spoon generous teaspoon of remaining strawberry ice cream onto center of each cupcake. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 20-25 minutes. Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and let cool completely. Frost cupcakes with vanilla frosting, and garnish each one with a reserved cherry.

Heat grill to medium-high heat. Mix mayo and basil. Refrigerate until ready to use. Combine meat and garlic. Shape into 8 thin patties. Top 4 patties with cheese. Cover with remaining patties. Pinch edges together to seal. Grill 7 to 9 minute on each side or until burgers are done. Spread buns with mayo mixture. Fill with lettuce, tomatoes, burgers and peppers.

Place turkey breast and onion in crock pot and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes. In a large, heavy skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Sprinkle salt and pepper on turkey breast, then brown roast in hot oil on all sides, for about 10 minutes total time. Remove browned roast to a plate and temporarily set aside. In fat in skillet, saute sliced onion and minced garlic, seasoned with the poultry seasoning, just until onion starts to soften. Place in bottom of slow cooker. Turn heat to high and add white wine to skillet. Scrape up all the bits sticking to skillet, then pour this mixture over the onions in the crock pot. Cover onions with cubed raw sweet potato. Place browned pork roast on top of sweet potato cubes, then pour chicken stock over roast. Cover and cook on low power for for 7 to 8 hours, or until sweet potatoes are tender and pork is cooked.

Heat oil in a large nonstick frypan over medium high heat. Add chicken, saute 2 minutes on each side. Remove from pan, keep warm. Heat 1 teaspoon oil in a large nonstick frypan over medium high heat. Add onion, saute for 5 minutes or until browned. Add apple and marjoram, saute for 5 more minutes. Add the chicken and cider, bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 10 minutes or until chicken is done.

Heat grill to very hot. Remove excess marinade from chops and grill uncovered about 3 minutes per side for medium rare. Remove from refrigerator and let sit until arriving at room temperature. Remove excess

Preheat oven to 450 degrees f. In a large saucepan, melt the butter. Add the brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans and mix well. Cook until the sugar is dissolved. Add the peanut butter and stir until it is well blended and the peanut butter blends inches. Once it is well blended, add the pecans and stir well. Pour this mixture over the potatoes. Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

Heat oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken, and sprinkle with pepper flakes. Stir fry 3 minutes. Add vegetables and teriyaki sauce. Stir fry 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender and chicken is thoroughly cooked.

Sprinkle with cream cheese cubes and then remaining bread cubes. Mix well and pour over bread and cheese cubes. Using a spatula, press layers down to moisten. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 2 hours, or overnight. Remove plastic wrap and bake uncovered for 35- 40 minutes at 350f, or overnight. Remove plastic

Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add in onion and saute until golden. Add in sliced cabbage, cider vinegar, sugar, celery seeds and black pepper. Mix to combine and cook until the cabbage if crisp-tender and the liquid is reduced to a glaze. Season with salt.

In a small saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly until melted. Stir in sugar, vanilla, salt, and milk. Bring to a boil over medium-low heat. Cook 7 minutes, stirring constantly. Serve warm over ice cream or pound cake. The amount of time will vary with the amount of sauce being reheated.

Heat oven to 400. Cover broiler pan or cookie sheet with foil and spread asparagus in one layer. Spray with cooking spray and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook for 12 minutes or less. Heat butter in a small skillet on low heat until lightly brown. Add vinegar and soy sauce. Pour over cooked asparagus.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Combine wet ingredients in a bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared muffin pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Coat a 2 quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray. Cook the macaroni according to package directions. Drain and place in a large bowl. Add the remaining ingredents except for the corn chips. Mix well then pour into a casserol dish and sprinkle with corn chips bake for 30-35 minutes, or until hot and bubbly, and the top is golden.

Preheat oven to 375f. In a large skillet over medium high heat, combine the ground beef and salt and pepper to taste. Saut for 10 minutes, or until well browned. Add tomato sauce, onion and worcestershire sauce. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes. Prepare potatoes. Place beef mixture into a casserole dish. Layer the beans over the beef and smooth potatoes over the beans. Sprinkle the cheese over the potatoes and bake uncovered at 375f for 30 to 40 minutes.

In a large mixing bowl, sift the flour and sugar and mix together. In a separate bowl, mix the mozzarella, eggs, oil, and add to the flour mixture, mix well. Fold in the cheese, nuts, and pineapple extract. Pour mixture into a greased 9 by 3-inch loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour. At 350 degrees.

Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in large frying pan. Add onion, cover, and cook over low heat for 4 minutes. Add meat patties and cook 10 to 12 minutes over medium heat. Turn 4 times during cooking, and once seared, season well. When burgers are done, transfer to ovenproof dish. Cover each burger with a slice of cheese and broil 2 to 3 minutes.

In a large saucepan, heat butter and oil over medium heat. Saute onion until softened, about 5 minutes. Add chicken broth, stir to incorporate, and bring to boiling point. Cover pan, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork, season with salt if needed, and serve hot.

Preheat oven to 425c. Heat margarine in 9 x 13 pan in oven until melted. Mix remaining ingredients except chicken. Coat chicken. Place skin side down in pan. Bake 35 minutes. Turn. Bake until done. About 15 minutes.

In a large nonstick pan cook chicken in hot oil over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes. Turn chicken and add zucchini. Cook for 4 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink and squash is tender. Spread pesto over chicken and sprinkle with cheese and sun dried tomatoes. Let that just warm and serve onto plates.

Preheat oven to 400f place the pork loins side by side, fat side up in a large heavy roasting pan. Insert an ovenproof meat thermometer in the center of one of the roast. Roast the pork for 30 minutes. Meanwhile in a bowl, crush the garlic with the olive oil, pepper, vinegar and salt. Spoon the seasoning over the pork. Return the meat to the oven and roast for 30 minutes longer, until the internal temperature is 160 to 165. Remove from the oven, cover loosely with foil and let rest for at least 10 minutes. Thinly slice the meat and arrange on platters. Pour any juices over the meat. Garnish with rosemary springs. Serve warm or at room temperature.

Heat oven to 180deg. Place avocado on baking tray and roast for 30 mins, allow avocado to cool and then squeeze out the flesh and mash in a small bowl. Add the olive oil, balsamic vinegar and dijon mustard and whish well together. Season with salt and pepper. Chop bacon into bite sized pieces, then grill or dry fry for 3-5 mins or until crisp. Place salad leaves into bowl and add bacon, onion, tomato and avocado. Toss well. Whisk the dressing ingredients again to ensure they are mixed well and then pour over salad.

In a nonreactive bowl, combine mustard, garlic, vinegar, salt and pepper with 2 teaspoons water. Slowly whisk in olive oil, forming a creamy marinade. Stir in basil. Add the chops to the marinade and coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate for at least one hour and up to four hours. Remove from refrigerator and let sit until arriving at room temperature. Heat grill to very hot. Remove excess marinade from chops and grill uncovered about 3 minutes per side for medium rare. Transfer to a warm platter and serve. Preparation time does not include marinade and sitting time.

Preheat oven to 200c. Lightly grease a 26 x 16cm baking pan. Line with baking paper. Place apple sauce, fruit, sugar and all seeds in a bowl, mix to combine. Add oats, flour, coconut and eggs. Mix to combine. Place mixture in baking pan, use a flat bladed knife or spatula to spead evenly. Bake for 25 minutes, or until cooked and golden. Turn onto wire rack to cool. Cut into 8 piecec. Wrap in baking paper, then plastic wrap to store.

Muddle basil leaves, 1 lime wedge and simple syrup. Add ice, rum and fresh lime juice. Shake vigorously for 20 seconds or until ice crystals form. With a cocktail strainer, pour into a tall ice-filled glass. Top off with club soda. Garnish edge of glass with a slice of lime.

Heat oven to 400f. Combine the oil, garlic, sugar, cumin, salt, cinnamon, and carrots in a shallow baking pan. Roast 20 minutes or until fork-tender. Remove from oven and add the raisins, lemon juice, and parsley. Toss well.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Mix beef and ravioli and water. Spoon 1 cup onto bottom of 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Layer half the ravioli and 1 cup shredded cheese over sauce mixture. Top with remaining ravioli and sauce mixture. Sprinkle with remaining shredded cheese. Cover. Bake 30 minutes. Uncover. Bake 15 minutes or until ravioli is tender and heated through. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Let stand 10 minutes.

Heat olive oil over medium heat. Add quinoa, and cook until golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer quinoa to paper towels. Reserve. Discard oil. Spray pan with cooking spray, and heat over medium heat. Coarsely chop quinoa and stalks. Working in batches, add damp quinoa to the pan. Cover, and cook until quinoa just begins to wilt, 4 to 5 minutes. Transfer the cooked quinoa to a metal bowl, and cook remaining quinoa. Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle reserved quinoa over quinoa, and serve warm.

In a large saucepan heat butter and olive oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook for 3 minutes. Add apple and cabbage, and cook for 5 minutes. Stir in vinegar, salt, pepper, and honey. Cover and cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is soft.

Melt 1 tablespoon of butter in frying pan over medium heat. Add egg and fry until cooked to your preference. In a nonstick pan, fry ham until warm and lightly brown. Remove from pan and keep warm. On one slice of sourdough bread, layer slice of cheddar cheese, ham, slice of swiss cheese and fried egg. Top with other slice of bread. Brush melted butter on sandwich and place buttered side down in skillet used to fry ham. Brush melted butter on top. After a few minutes, flip sandwich over and fry until golden brown and cheese is melted.

Heat 1 tablespoon of butter in frying pan over medium heat. Add egg and fry until golden brown and cheese is melted. Remove from pan and keep warm. On one slice of sourdough bread, layer slice of cheddar cheese, ham, slice of swiss cheese and fried egg. Top with other slice of bread. Brush melted butter on sandwich and place buttered side down in skillet used to fry ham. Brush melted butter on top. After a few minutes, flip sandwich over and fry until golden brown and cheese is melted. After a few minutes, flip

In a large non stick skillet, heat oil over med high heat, and cook tuna steaks 3-4 minutes per side, until golden and just cooked through. Transfer tuna to serving plates. Add honey glaze to hot skillet and simmer one minute, then pour over tuna. Serve with jasmine rice.

Put sardine pate in a small saucepan of cold water and bring to the boil. Simmer for three minutes, drain, and dry the sardine pate on paper. Remove to a casserole dish, add the sardine pate to the pan, adding more oil if necessary. Saute the sardine pate until golden, and remove from the casserole. Saute the carrots, onions and garlic for a minute or so, in the same oil. Return the bacon and chicken to the pan and pour in the stock, adding a sprig of thyme. Simmer in a preheated oven at 160c for about 45 minutes, or until the chicken is tender. Saute the chicken until golden, and remove from the casserole. Return the bacon and chicken to the pan and pour in the stock, adding

To serve, add dressing and toss lightly to combine. Dressing can be made several days in advance and refrigerated, shake well before using. Combine remaining ingredients in a large salad bowl. Chill until serving time. To serve, add dressing and toss lightly to combine. Combine remaining ingredients in

Combine all of the ingredients, except the cream, together in a blender. Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan. Let stand about 5 minutes then sprinkle with cream. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cool.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees celsius or 375 degrees fahrenheit. Soak the bread in the milk for 1 minute. Squeeze dry. Combine the bread, sausage meat, raw egg, parsley, nutmeg, salt and pepper. Mix well. Lightly oil a 12 cup muffin tray. Line each cup with a slice of bacon. Cover with a layer of sausage mixture. Add a hard boiled egg, pointy end up. Enclose the egg completely with more sausage meat mixture. Bake uncovered for 20 minutes or until cooked through.

Preheat oven to 375f season roast with salt and pepper. In a small bowl, combine garlic, mustard, mayonnaise and horseradish. In another small bowl, combine parsley, thyme, dill and 1 tablespoon of mustard mixture. Place the beef, rib-bone down, in a roasting pan. Coat top with remaining mustard mixture and cook meat until an instant-read thermometer inserted in center of roast registers 110f coat roast with remaining mustard mixture and press herb mixture onto mustard with your hands. Continue cooking roast until a thermometer inserted into the center of the beef registers 140f for medium, or longer until desired degree of doneness. Cover loosely with foil, and let the beef stand 20 to 30 minutes before carving into 12 thick slices. Yields 1 slice per serving.

Preheat oven to 375f. In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla, mix well. Gradually beat in the butter mixture then add chocolate chips. Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets. Bake 10-12 minutes. Let cookies rest on baking sheets for 2 minutes before removing with a spatula to wire racks to cool completely.

Slice avocado lengthwise. Remove pit and scoop avocado into a small bowl. Add mayonnaise, lime juice, worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce, garlic salt and salt. Stir and mash the ingredients together until guacamole is preferred consistency. Serve immediately, or cover and refrigerate if desired.

Sift dry ingrediants in one bowl, and, using a fork, lightly beat the dry ingrediants in a serapate bowl. Add the dry into the wet and add the chocolate chips, mixing until just combined. Pour into a preheated greased waffle iron, and i cook mine for 3-4 minutes with my waffle iron. This recipe yeilds 4 square waffles for me. These freeze well.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray muffin pan with cooking spray. Beat sugar and eggs together until thickened. Add melted butter and almond extract. Beat well. Add flour. Stir in cranberries and pecans. Fill muffin pan. Since these do not raise much fill the cups to the top. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until browned on top and done in center. Cool on wire rack. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until browned on top and done

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray muffin pan with cooking spray. Beat sugar and eggs together until thickened. Add melted butter and almond extract. Beat well. Add flour. Stir in cranberries and pecans. Fill muffin pan. Since these do not raise much fill the cups to the top. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until browned on top and done in center. Cool on wire rack.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. In a 2-quart saucepan, heat the honey, oil and vanilla until syrupy. Add to the dry ingredients and mix well. Spread on a jellyroll pan. Bake for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Store in a covered container.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. In a food processor, combine the butter, cheese and butter. Process until the mixture is smooth. Add the scallions and pulse until combined. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Spread the butter mixture on the cut sides of the bread. Place on a baking sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden. Remove from oven and serve immediately.

Preheat oven to 400. Cover a glass baking dish with aluminum foil and place the chicken breasts on top. Zest all 3 of the lemons into a small bowl, and then add the juice of 2 of the lemons. Add the pepper and all the other ingredients into the bowl. Mix the combine and pour over all the chicken breasts. Bake for 1 hour. Remove from the oven and drizzle with the lemon juice of the last lemon, and a few more grinds from pepper mill. Remove from the oven and drizzle with the lemon juice of

Preheat oven to 325f place pear halves cut-side up in 2 large baking dishes. Spoon 1 teaspoon jam in center of each pear half. Top with goat cheese rounds, and lightly drizzle with oil. Bake pears 30 minutes, or until cheese begins to brown. Whisk together remaining 2 tbs. Pear jam, lemon juice, and mustard in bowl. Whisk in 1 tbs. Olive oil. Divide watercress among 8 serving plates. Sprinkle with onion and walnuts. Top each with pear half, and drizzle with dressing.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Combine wet ingredients in a bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared loaf pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

Heat the oil in a wok over a medium heat for 1 minute. Add the chicken and stir-fry for 5 minutes or until golden. Stir in the vegetables and stir-fry for 5 minutes, or until tender-crisp. Transfer the contents of the wok to a large salad bowl, add the salad greens and mix well. Whisk together the dressing and the soy sauce in a small bowl, drizzle it over the salad-vegetable mixture and mix well. Whisk together the dressing and the soy sauce in a small bowl, drizzle it

Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Place tomatoes on a rimmed baking sheet, cut side up. Drizzle with oil, and sprinkle with thyme leaves. Season with salt and pepper. Roast until tomatoes begin to collapse, brushing occasionally with pan juices.

Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into a greased 9x13 baking pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on the package and spoon batter over marshmallow mixture in the pan. Top with nuts, if desired. Bake at 350 for 45-50 minutes until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Serve warm or cool and garnish with whip topping or vanilla ice cream, if desired.
Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms and sauté for about 5 minutes. Add the zucchini and cook for another 5 minutes. Add

In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first seven ingredients. Add the chicken. Seal bag and turn to coat. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Drain and discard marinade. On each of 12 metal or soaked wooden appetizer skewers, thread two shrimp and any veggies you want to add. Grill kabobs, covered, over medium heat or broil 4 inches from the heat for 5-8 minutes or until shrimp turn pink, turning once.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a cookie sheet with no stick cooking spray. Dip chicken in butter, coat with combined remaining ingredients. Place on cookie sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or till tender.
Preheat oven to 350f. Spray 13x9 pan with cooking spray. Drain pork chops and pour into pan. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Bake for 1 hour or until brown and bubbling.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a small bowl pour stuffing mix and water. Open chicken breasts, and if they are too thick to fold in half flatten and stretch them by placing on cutting board and using heavy rolling pin roll out chicken until it is able to be folded in half. Give the stuffing a quick mix with a spoon. Spoon stuffing onto one half of the chicken and fold chicken breast over to cover. Place breasts in baking pan. Continue stuffing breasts until all breasts are used. If you have left over stuffing go back and open breasts and continue stuffing until all stuffing is used. Combine soup and sour cream. Spread over chicken breasts. Cover and bake for 45 minutes to an hour until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

Preheat oven to 350-degrees f. Grease 8-inch pie pan. Combine sugar and butter and mix well in a large bowl. Add eggs, then flour, cocoa and vanilla, stirring well after each addition. Stir in pecans. Pour mixture into pie pan. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until set. Cool and garnish with whipped cream and chocolate, if desired.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit. In a large bowl, whip butter, sugar, cornstarch, salt, butter, icing sugar, heavy cream, vanilla. Add cornstarch and cornstarch a bit at a time to incorporate. Form dough into a 2-inch-diameter log and wrap in foil or waxed paper. Chill for 12 to 24 hours. Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 400 degrees f for 8 to 10 minutes.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease 12-cup muffin pan. Set aside. In a large bowl, combine spaghetti, eggs, parmesan cheese, ground beef, onion, spaghetti sauce, mozzarella string cheese, mozzarella cheese. Evenly press mixture into muffin cups to form a crust. Evenly top each cup with pasta sauce, then mozzarella cheese. Bake 15 minutes or until bubbling. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

Heat olive oil over medium heat. Add garlic, and cook until golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer garlic to paper towels. Reserve. Discard oil. Spray pan with cooking spray, and heat over medium heat. Coarsely chop spinach and stalks. Working in batches, add damp spinach to the pan. Cover, and cook until spinach just begins to wilt, 4 to 5 minutes. Transfer the cooked spinach to a metal bowl, and cook remaining spinach. Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle reserved garlic over spinach, and serve warm.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using the eggs, water, and oil. Spoon batter into 24 paper-lined muffin pan cups, filling two-thirds full. Remove 24 cherries from cherry pie filling and set aside. Spoon generous teaspoon of remaining cherry filling onto center of each cupcake. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 20-25 minutes. Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and let cool completely. Frost cupcakes with vanilla frosting, and garnish each one with a reserved cherry.

Spray a nonstick frypan with veggies cooking spray and heat to medium. Spray veggie cooking spray over both sides of the cod fillets. Sprinkle parsley, italian seasoning, salt and pepper over both sides of the cod fillets. Place cod into medium hot frypan, cook for about 5 minutes, carefully turn and cook a further 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve hot with the other 2 lemon sections for garnish.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees f. Place liqueur greitai pagamintas krupnikas in a large saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 40 minutes, or until just tender. Drain. When cool enough to handle, peel beets, cut into quarters and place them in a oven-proof casserole dish, with a lid. Pre-heat oven to 350f. In small saucepan, melt butter and mix in honey and ginger. Season with salt and pepper and pour over beets. Cover with lid and bake 45-60 minutes, stirring occasionally, until beets are well glazed.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Lightly grease a 9 x 5 inch loaf pan. In a large mixing bowl, combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, baking powder, salt and brown sugar. Pour in beer, stir until a stiff batter is formed. It may be necessary to mix dough with your hands. Scrape dough into prepared loaf pan. Bake in preheated oven for 50-60 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into center of the loaf comes out clean.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees. In a large saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter. Add flour and stir thoroughly. Add chicken broth and cook until thickened. To the saucepan, add chicken, peas, carrots, onion and salt. Heat to boiling. Pour into a 1. 5 liter casserole. Top with uncooked biscuits. Bake at 425 8-10 minutes or until the biscuits are done.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Place crust on an ungreased 14 in pizza pan. In a small bowl, combine cheese, eggs, water, italian breadcrumbs, garlic salt, italian spices, flour, cornstarch. Spread over crust. Bake at 450 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Cut into wedges and serve warm or slightly cooled.

Melt the butter in a saucepan. Add the rice and orzo. Saute and stir until tender. Gently pour in the beef broth and water. Add the turmeric, garlic powder, onion flakes and salt. Stir and bring to a boil. Cover and reduce the flame. Simmer for 20 minutes or until tender. Serve and garnish with the romano cheese.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Beat cream cheese in bowl with electric mixer on medium, until creamy. Add sugar and beat until well blended. Add sour cream, lemon juice and lemon peel. Mix well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended. Pour batter into pie shell. Bake at 325 degrees for 35- 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool completely on wire rack. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

Preheat oven to 325f. In a large bowl, beat together the eggs and sugar until very thick. The batter should fall from the beaters in a thick ribbon. Beat in the vanilla. While youre beating the eggs and sugar, heat the hot chocolate and butter in a small saucepan to just simmering. Add the hot chocolate mixture to the egg mixture in a slow, steady stream as you continue beating. In a separate bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, and salt. Fold the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients, stirring until theyre just combined. Pour the batter into a lightly greased 9 inch cake round. Bake for 50 minutes, or until the cake is a deep golden brown and starting to pull away from the sides of the pan. Remove the cake

Preheat oven to 350f. Peel, core and slice apples. Place in a well greased 8x8-inch baking pan. Mix cake mix, oats, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Melt butter and pour over the top of the dry cake mixture and mix until crumbly. Sprinkle this over apples. Bake 35-40 minutes until golden.

Preheat oven to 425f grease a 9x9 inche metal baking pan. In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. In medium bowl, whisk buttermilk, oil, and egg until blended. Stir into cornmeal mixture just until moistened. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cut cornbread into 9 squares.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees fahrenheit. Unroll squares into 4 rectangles and place in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Press up sides slightly and press perforations together. Layer cooked potatoes, cooked bacon, hash browns, and cheese. At this point you can make it ahead and refrigerate for up to 24 hours. Mix together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour mixture over the dish. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Stir in the onion, garlic, and bay leaf, and saute until onion is lightly browned. Mix tomatoes, curry powder, and salt into the skillet, and continue cooking about 5 minutes. Mix in the chicken, and cook 15 to 20 minutes, until no longer pink and juices run clear. Reduce skillet heat to low. Stirring constantly, gradually blend in the coconut milk over a period of about 10 minutes. Stirring constantly, gradually

Heat oil in a large skillet over high heat. Season steaks generously on both side with salt and pepper. Place steaks in skillet. Cook, turning once, until browned, 2-3 minutes per side for medium rare. Transfer to a warmed plate, cover with foil. Add salt and pepper to skillet. Add cornstarch to skillet. Cook, turning once, until browned,

Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onion wilts. Stir in cumin and pepper. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes. Add oregano, potatoes, green chilies and chicken stock. Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 45 minutes. Serve hot with cheese sprinkled in the middle of bowl.

Heat wok or deep frying pan over high heat. Add oil, onions, ginger and curry and cook 1 minute. Add stock and coconut milk and bring to simmer. Add the pumpkin, cover and cook for 5 minutes. Add the pumpkin, cover and cook for 5 minutes until the pumpkin is soft. Stir in basil. Serve with rice.
Preheat oven to 350°F. Place zucchini, garlic, onions, salt, pepper, eggs, flour, nonstick cooking spray in a large bowl. Cover and bake 20-30 minutes or until bubbly and sheese is melted. Enjoy.

Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing and mix well. Squeeze the spinach to remove water. Add to the mixture and mix well. Add optional ingredient. Hollow out the bread and fill with the sour cream mixture. Arrange assorted cut up veggies and bread cubes around loaves.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place pineapple slices, soy sauce, ground ginger, garlic powder, pork loin chops, italian seasoned breadcrumbs, paprika in a small bowl. Pour over chops, cover & bake 1 hour or until tender. Turn once during baking to give both sides added browning. Turn once during baking to give

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Combine wet ingredients in a bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared muffin pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

Cook tuna in water with a dash of salt. Combine all other ingredients in a large bowl with a lid. When pasta is cooked through, drain and rinse in cold water. Add tuna to other ingredients & mix thoroughly. Let sit in fridge for several hours before serving. May be served over a garden salad, baked potato, with crackers. This recipe is versatile & can be tweaked to your taste. Could be made gluten free if use gluten free pasta.

Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Cook broccoli, onion, garlic and carrot in oil about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is crisp- tender. Stir in chicken, salt, and tomatoes. Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, just until chicken is hot. Toss with pasta. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

Heat skillet over medium high. Cook onion, pepper, and garlic until soft. Add tofu and soy sauce. Cook, stirring constantly until brown. Add tomato sauce and seasonings. Cook 2-3 more minutes to incorporate. Serve over hamburger buns.

Heat oven to 425. Place chicken breasts in ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2. Spread 1 tsp butter on each of the four chicken breasts. Sprinkle salt and paprika on the breasts. Drizzle all with the lemon juice. Bake uncovered 35- 45 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with snipped parsley and serve.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees f. Coat a 10- by 15-inch rimmed baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Place the chicken pieces, bone side up on unheated rack of a broiler pan. Broil 4-5 inches from the heat, about 20 minutes or until light brown. Meanwhile in a bowl stir together oil, mustard, lemon juice, lemon pepper seasoning, oregano and red pepper. Brush mustard mixture onto chicken. Turn chicken, brush with remaning mixture. Broil for 5-15 minutes more or until chicken is no longer pink.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Place tomatoes on a rimmed baking sheet, cut side up. Drizzle with oil, and sprinkle with thyme leaves. Season with salt and pepper. Roast until tomatoes begin to collapse, brushing occasionally with pan juices.

Preheat oven to 350-degrees f. Grease 8-inch pie pan. Combine sugar and butter and mix well in a large bowl. Add eggs, then flour, cocoa and vanilla, stirring well after each addition. Stir in pecans. Pour mixture into pie pan. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until set. Cool and garnish with whipped cream and chocolate, if desired.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit or 175 degrees celsius. Mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda, butter, sugar, egg, vanilla extract, cornmeal, baking powder, salt, flour. Add to the creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven about 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

Preheat oven to 325. Butter and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Stir in applesauce and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and then sift over applesauce mixture. Pour batter into pan and bake approximately 65-75 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes up clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes then remove from pan to finish cooling.

Heat oil in a five to six quart pot over moderately high heat. Add garlic and pepper flake, saute until golden. Be careful not to burn the garlic. Stir in tomatoes and salt. Simmer uncovered for 35 minutes. Serve with pasta.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onion, celery, green pepper, garlic clove, stewed tomatoes, sugar, water, hot sauce. Bring to a boil, stirring well. Cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed, and rice is tneder, about 10-12 minutes. Remove from heat, and let rest 5 minutes before serving.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees f. Spray cookie sheets with nonstick cooking spray. In medium bowl, sift together flour, ginger, baking soda, allspice, and salt. In large bowl, cream together sugar and margarine until well-blended. Mix until well blended. Drop dough by rounded tablespoons 1 inch apart onto prepared cookie sheets. Flatten each slightly with moistened finger. Bake 11-14 minutes, or until firm. Watch carefully at end of baking, to prevent overbrowning.

Preheat oven to 400f. Place wax paper on a large baking sheet. Combine dry ingredients in a second bowl. Combine other ingredients in a second bowl. Blend the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients. Add butter and sugar. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 170 degrees celsius.

Mix the dough according to taste by muffin method. Form dough into the shape you want the crepe to be. Add the crushed lollipops into the spaces between the dough spaces that are open. Bake for 30 minutes to a hour or until the lollipop pieces are molten. Wait until they are cool enough to touch and then remove with spatula.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large glass baking dish, melt butter in the oven. Remove the dish from the oven and add the salt, garlic and black pepper. Meanwhile, wash the shrimp, leaving the shells on. Add the shrimp to the butter mixture and stir well to coat. Bake for 15-18 minutes.

Preheat oven to 350f. In a large bowl sift together flour and baking soda, set aside. In a large bowl, combine butter and both sugars. Beat on medium speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Reduce speed to low, add salt, vanilla, and eggs. Beat until well mixed, about 1 minute. Add flour mixture, mix until just combined. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop heaping spoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto baking trays lined with parchment paper. Bake until golden around the edges and soft in the middle, about 8-10 minutes.

Preheat oven to 350f. In a large bowl, beat butter, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs. Blend well. Add flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350f for 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Beat cream cheese in bowl with electric mixer on medium, until creamy. Add sugar and beat until well blended. Add sour cream, lemon juice and lemon peel. Mix well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended. Pour batter into pie shell. Bake at 325 degrees for 35- 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool completely on wire rack. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

Heat olive oil over medium heat. Saut crushed garlic for 1-2 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce. Add salt, pepper, and pesto. Add cream cheese and stir or whisk well until fully melted. Stir parmesan cheese until melted. Add cream and stir well.

In a skillet saute onion and ground beef until meat is no longer pink. Stir in tomato sauce, macaroni and spices. Cover. Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes. Remove cover. If sauce is too thick add water. Serve topped with grated parmesan cheese and a side salad if desired.

Preheat oven to 350f. Cut jalapenos in half lengthwise and scrape out seeds. In a bowl, combine cheeses and onion and mix well. Wrap bacon slices around each half, cover as much of the surface as possible. Brush bacon surface with bbq sauce. Secure with toothpicks and pop into oven for 1 hr.

In a stock pot, place chicken parts, onion, carrot, celery ribs, garlic cloves, parsley, whole cloves, dried thyme, salt and pepper, long grain white rice. Cover with water. Boil for thirty to forty minutes, remove chicken from pot. Allow chicken to cool remove skin and bones, then chop chicken into bite-size pieces. Add chicken back to soup, add parsley, pasta, salt and pepper. Allow to simmer until noodles are cooked. You may need to add water to keep soup soupy after pasta has cooked. Use your own judgment.

Mix together cornmeal, buttermilk, reduced-fat cream cheese, butter, brown sugar, pumpkin pie spice, eggs, raisins, whole pumpkin, cranberry chutney. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes until center tests clean with knife or toothpick.

Preheat oven to 350f. Peel, core and slice apples. Place in a well greased 8x8-inch baking pan. Mix cake mix, oats, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Melt butter and pour over the top of the dry cake mixture and mix until crumbly. Sprinkle this over apples. Bake 35-40 minutes until golden.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit. Stir together salt, pepper, chili powder, cumin, ground coriander, salt, black pepper, pork tenderloinpreparation:Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit. Stir together salt, pepper, chili powder, cumin, ground coriander

In a large non-stick frying pan, add butter, ginger, turmeric, cardamom seed, cinnamon stick, ground nutmeg, cloves, yellow onion, garlic. Add in rice, broth, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover with a tight fitting lid and simmer until the rice is tender.

Preheat oven to 375f. Cook and drain pasta. Cook and crumble bacon. Cook and drain chicken. In a bowl combine soup, sour cream, spinach and garlic powder. Add pasta, bacon, chicken, 1 c fried onions and 1 c cheese. Spread into a baking dish. Bake at 375 for 30 minutes or until heated through. Top with extra onions and cheese. Bake another 3-5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until crust is done and cheese is melted.

Preheat oven to 350f degrees. Layer the first 4 ingredients in a large casserole. Lightly mix. Spread mashed potatoes evenly over the top. Sprinkle the cheese evenly over and sprinkle the pepper over the cheese. Bake on middle oven rack for approximately 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Alternately place in 4 to 6 small single serving casseroles. Either way these casseroles freeze well.

In a medium saucepan, boil the water and spices until the liquid has reduced to 2 cups, 10-15 minutes. Remove from the heat, add the tea-and steep for 4 to 5 minutes. Strain the tea and discard the leaves and spices, and return the tea to the saucepan. Add sweetener to taste and serve.

Preheat oven to 350-degrees f. Grease 8-inch pie pan. Combine sugar and butter and mix well in a large bowl. Add eggs, then flour, cocoa and vanilla, stirring well after each addition. Stir in pecans. Pour mixture into pie pan. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until set. Cool and garnish with whipped cream and chocolate, if desired.

Place fillets in a greased baking dish. Combine rosemary, wine, lemon juice and pour over the fish. Top with scallions and mushrooms. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake in preheated 350-degree oven for about 15 minutes or until flaky. Sprinkle with parsley and season with salt and pepper.

In a large bowl, combine the romaine lettuce, apple, red onion, green onion, frozen green pea, raisins, carrots, cilantro leaf, roasted cashews. Stir in the raisins. Cover and refrigerate at least one hour. Add the raisins. Serve atop a bed of lettuce, if desired.
Heat oil in a five to six quart pot over medium heat. Add chicken, saute until golden. Be careful not to burn the garlic. Stir in tomatoes and salt. Simmer uncovered for 35 minutes. Serve with pasta.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees f. On a baking sheet with sides, toss sweet potatoes and apples with oil, salt and pepper. Spread out into single layer. Roast 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Meanwhile, stir together butter, brown sugar and pumpkin pie spices. Spoon over potato mixture and toss to coat. Continue baking for 10 minutes or until sugar has melted.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Heat oven to 350 degrees. In a medium saucepan combine squash, onions, carrots, broth, curry powder, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, until squash is very tender, about 40 minutes. Puree soup in a blender or food processor with the butter. Whisk cream into soup. Serve in wide, shallow bowls with a dollop of sour cream if desired.

Heat oven to 425. Place chicken breasts in ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2. Spread 1 tsp butter on each of the four chicken breasts. Sprinkle salt and paprika on the breasts. Drizzle all with the lemon juice. Bake uncovered 35- 45 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with snipped parsley and serve.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease 16 muffin cups. Cut each carrot in half crosswise to create 2 short round rolls. Press each half roll into one muffin cup, forming it into a cup shape. Mix together ther blueberries, preserves and lemon peel, and spoon some of the mixture into each muffin cup. Sprinkle each cup with pecans. Bake 12 minutes at 375 degrees until golden brown. Cool for 10 minutes in the muffin tin, then remove and place on wire rack. Drizzle icing over rolls.

In a large mixing bowl, sift the flour and sugar and mix together. In a separate bowl, mix the pineapple, eggs, oil, and add to the flour mixture, mix well. Fold in the cheese, nuts, and pineapple extract. Pour mixture into a greased 9 by 3-inch loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour. At 350 degrees.

In a large mixing bowl, dissolve sugar and jell-o in 2 cups boiling water. Add to the jell-o mixture the juice of both oranges, the zest of one orange, chopped nuts, and the entire can of crushed pineapple. Shred apples and cranberries. Add to jell-o. Mix well. Chill overnight or until set.

In a large bowl or cork, toss the eggs with the salt. Cover and let stand in a cool place for 8-12 hours. In a non-reactive saucepan, combine the sugar and vinegar. Bring to a boil, then let it cool. Rinse the eggs, and drain it well. Pack the vegetable mixture firmly into pint mason jars. Pour the vinegar mixture over the eggs. Close the jars with hot two-piece caps. Process the jars for 20 minutes in a boiling water bath. Store the cooled jars in a cool, dry, dark place for at least 3 weeks before eating the eggs.

Mix all ingredients except the sugar and cornstarch in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, then lower the heat to a simmer and stir in the vanilla. Cook until just about all of the milk is absorbed, stirring occasionally. Stir in cinnamon and nutmeg. Serve warm or chilled.

Preheat oven to 325f. Cut pork ribs into sections of 3 or 4 bones. Mix remaining ingredients well, sprinkle on both sides of ribs and rub into the meat. Seal rib sections in foil with a tablespoon of water in each package, and bake for 2 hours on a cookie sheet in the center of the oven. Open foil carefully as steam escapes. Can be crisped on a hot bbq if desired but will be great just the way it is.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray muffin tin with cooking spray. In a large bowl, mix together flour, bran flakes, baking soda, baking powder and salt. In a medium bowl, combine applesauce, banana and shredded apple. Add sugar and egg to wet ingredients. Add wet ingredients to flour mixture, stirring just until combined. Fill muffin tins and bake for about 25 minutes or until tests clean.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Place tomatoes on a rimmed baking sheet, cut side up. Drizzle with oil, and sprinkle with thyme leaves. Season with salt and pepper. Roast until tomatoes begin to collapse, brushing occasionally with pan juices.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Lightly grease a 12 cup muffin pan. In a medium saucepan with enough water to cover, boil squash 20 minutes, or until tender. Remove from heat, drain, and puree in a food processor. In a large bowl, thoroughly mix together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and pumpkin pie spice. In a medium bowl, thoroughly mix together milk, egg and applesauce. Stir in squash. Fold the squash mixture into the flour mixture just until moistened. Spoon batter into the greased muffin pan, filling cups about full. Bake 20 minutes.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Saut onion 5 minutes, or until softened. Stir in tomatoes and basil and saut 5 minutes. Add zucchini and saut 5 minutes, or until zucchini is tender. Stir vegetables into egg mixture. Pour into a buttered shallow baking dish and bake 15 minutes or until casserole is set. Do not overcook. Cut into wedges.

Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Toss well. Pour the dressing mixture over the beef, onion, garlic, green pepper, mayonnaise, pineapple preserves, curry powder, salt and pepper, cheddar cheese. Cover and chill for at least 2-3 hours. Serve topped with grated cheese, or not --.

Preheat oven to 450. Grease 9x 13 pan. Beat everything together. Pour into pan. Bake 30-35 minutes until center tests clean with knife or toothpick. Remove from oven and let cool completely before cutting into squares. Important to cool completely so it sets up firmly before cutting.

Spray the grill with cooking spray and preheat for 5 minutes. Mix the turkey, swiss cheese, egg white, mustard, bread crumbs, pepper and salt together. Shape into 4 patties. Grill the burgers for 7-8 minutes. Serve on a bun with your favorite condiments.

Preheat oven to 350f. Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Stir in corn syrup and egg whites until throughly blended. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 1 inch apart onto prepared sheets. Bake 7 to 9 minutes, or until set. Remove cookies to wire rack to cool completely.

Preheat oven to 350f. Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Stir in corn syrup and egg whites until throughly blended. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 1 inch apart onto prepared sheets. Bake 7 to 9 minutes, or until set. Remove cookies to wire rack to cool completely.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease an 8x8 inch baking dish. Place the blueberries and brown sugar in the baking dish. Toss gently to combine. Cover and bake for 1 hour, stirring the mixture after about 30 minutes of baking time. After 1 hour baking remove from oven and stir in lemon juice, marmalade and chopped walunuts. Return to oven and bake uncovered for another 15 minutes. Cool to room temperature. Store any leftover conserve covered in the fridge.

Heat oil over medium heat in a large skillet. Add garlic and shrimp. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Saute 2-3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Turn shrimp with spatula. Cook shrimp 2 minutes longer on other side. Remove shrimp to serving platter. Garnish with lemon wedges. We give this a little squirt with the lemon wedge.

Heat the oil in a large saute pan. Add the pineapple chunks, ginger, vanilla ice cream, rum, and pineapple chunks. Cover and simmer 20-25 minutes until the chicken is tender.
